    {
      "name": "Ride",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/environment/people/cavalry.webp",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><p>A creature can take the Ride move action only while mounted on another creature. When a creature takes the Ride move action, they cause their mount to move up to the mount’s speed, taking the rider with them. Alternatively, a creature can use the Ride move action to have their mount use the Disengage move action as a free triggered action. A creature can use the Ride move action only once per round. A mounted creature can only have this move action applied to them once per round. This movement can be broken up with the rider’s bonus action and main action however they wish.</p></p>",
          "chat": ""
        },
